66.5	Billy_Graham	Billy Graham	William Franklin "Billy" Graham, Jr. (born November 7, 1918) is an American evangelical Christian evangelist, who rose to celebrity status as his sermons were broadcast on radio and television. Graham has been spiritual adviser to several United States Presidents and has met with 12, dating back to Harry S. Truman. He has repeatedly been on Gallup's most admired man and woman poll, and is listed at number seven for the 20th century (taken in 1999). He was ordained by the Southern Baptist Convention.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Billy_Graham_008.jpg/220px-Billy_Graham_008.jpg
